<br>
You guys notice a hand is covered, but no comments about the whole leg missing?<br>
<br>
Seriously, the more I read, the more I tend to agree with the people who say I shouldn't have rolled on the pally book.  My heart was in the right place (trying to aid a friend).  But it wasn't the best thought out decision.  <br>
<br>
Honestly though, My gripe was with the change of rules.  I would have been as torqued if the loot had been a vial of dragon blood (don't know if it exists, just a random item).  I didn't stand to profit from the item I was seeking to roll on, so the loot wasn't that big of a deal no matter what it was.  <br>
<br>
Hopefully someone will read this, and take away the idea that whatever raid you're gonna run, and however you choose to do it, once the rules are set, stick to em.  I have run several pickup raids in the past, and I know how frustraiting it can be, but there's no excuse for renigging on your word.  Make a plan, modify it if need be before you get under way, but once the raid starts stick with it.  For good or for ill, let your yes be yes and your no be no, not your yes be yes until you change your mind.<br>
<br>
Anyway, that's my 2cp, and I appreciate the thoughtout and constructive replies to this thread, and I hope that in the future more threads might follow the constructive path many here tried to take and less might attempt the combative stance others sought out. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://groups.msn.com/_Secure/0MwDcAoASbuI7OZ5yIceHaP39Dwigymrw7YcJinaML1euPtuElY352BHSRnfdaGxIsA33DsXknCipg2THJfvTtg/tenabrielcopy.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
